Package com.launchdarkly.sdk.internal.fdv2.payloads

This package contains FDv2 payload types and event handling.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DeleteObject
    Represents the delete-object event, which contains a payload object that should be deleted.
    Error
    Represents the error event, which indicates an error encountered server-side affecting the payload transfer.
    FDv2Event
    Represents an FDv2 event.
    Goodbye
    Represents the goodbye event, which indicates that the server is about to disconnect.
    IntentCode.IntentCodeTypeAdapter
    Gson TypeAdapter for serializing and deserializing IntentCode.
    PayloadTransferred
    Represents the payload-transferred event, which is sent after all messages for a payload update have been transmitted.
    PutObject
    Represents the put-object event, which contains a payload object that should be accepted with upsert semantics.
    ServerIntent
    Represents the server-intent event, which is the first message sent by flag delivery upon connecting to FDv2.
    ServerIntent.ServerIntentPayload
    Description of server intent to transfer a specific payload.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    IntentCode
    Represents the intent code indicating how the server intends to transfer data.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    FDv2Event.FDv2EventTypeMismatchException
    Exception thrown when attempting to deserialize an FDv2Event as the wrong event type.

Package com.launchdarkly.sdk.internal.fdv2.payloads Description

This package contains FDv2 payload types and event handling.

All types in this package are for internal LaunchDarkly use only, and are subject to change. They are not part of the public supported API of the SDKs, and they should not be referenced by application code. They have public scope only because they need to be available to LaunchDarkly SDK code in other packages.
